  "text": "The dimensionless extraction yield and monoterpene content (relative to fresh fruits) for each assay (Table 1) are shown in Figure 6 . The relative value was calculated in accordance with [CITATION_1] , with a relative value closer to 1.0 being more ideal in terms of drying performance. Figure 6 shows that the extraction yield and monoterpene content are close to 1.0 when drying is performed at mild temperatures (assays 1, 3, and 5). In contrast, drying at higher temperatures (assays 2, 4, and 6) decreases the extraction yield and monoterpene content, as compared with values obtained from fresh fruits. Therefore, drying at higher temperatures may reduce the extraction yield and monoterpene content of the essential oil from S. terebinthifolius fruits.",
